contrib\debian\manpages\centd.1:
    1: .TH BITCOINGREEND "22" "June 2026" "centd 1.1.1.1"
    3: cent \- peer-to-peer network based digital currency
    5: centd [options] <command> [params]
    7: centd [options] help <command> \- Get help for a command
    9: This  manual page documents the centd program. cent is a peer-to-peer digital currency. Peer-to-peer (P2P) means that there is no central authority to issue new money or keep track of transactions. Instead, these tasks are managed collectively by the nodes of the network. Advantages:
   11: cent can be sent easily through the Internet, without having to trust middlemen. Transactions are designed to be irreversible. Be safe from instability caused by fractional reserve banking and central banks. The limited inflation of the cent system’s money supply is distributed evenly (by CPU power) throughout the network, not monopolized by banks.
   16: Specify configuration file (default: cent.conf)
  180:     *note: requires cent 1.0.0.1 or later.
  192: Stops the cent server.
  204: cent.conf(5)

